+Rating

-Rating


I liked this a lot. I'm glad to see this hit the mainlist after hearing cryptic whispers about it for the past month or so.

Parts of the documentation came off as clunky, and there were some issues I had with the dialogue (see Critique section below), but they were not enough to detract from the article as a whole.

I especially liked the changing images. I've seen the  image swap trick before, but leading to an entire offset was unexpected. Afterwards, I went through and enlarged every image to find if anything was different. I was not disappointed.

+1, pretty easily.



~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

+Long]

-Long]


There's one general SPaG comment that I don't have the time nor effort to manually point out each instance of: a lot of commas are missing throughout the dialogue sections. I understand that, to replicate naturalistic speech, some commas can be sacrificedbut there are many cases in this article where it would actually have a verbal pause where a comma has been left out.

Anyways, on to some specific lines:



SCP-5045 is a virtual reality game that is compatible with most virtual reality headsets titled 
附加记录：    

Makes it sound like SCP-5045 is compatible with . I obviously know what you meant, but the wording is jarring. I recommend restructuring it as:



SCP-5045 is a virtual reality game titled  that is compatible with most virtual reality headsets.
附加记录：    





Within the farmhouse is a crudely drawn humanoid entity, with slightly more visual detail then  the goats,
附加记录：    

Than.





D-1711:  Very well then.
附加记录：    

Feels wooden.





D-1711:  Alright… uhh, everything's all black and outlined in these bright neon colors [snip]
附加记录：    

They're rattling off the exact details from the Description section. You can afford to cut most of this and leave it as .





SCP-5045-1:  Very well then.
附加记录：    

Another , but this one feels a bit more characteristic. Doesn't really fit the Texan drawl, I don't think, but that might be me.





D-6770:  My name is ████████ ██████. What's yours?
附加记录：    

That's two names under those blackboxes. It would be weird to meet someone who's mid-panic attack and give them your full name.





D-6770:  -nd it's always nice to have company, you know? I'm glad you're here.
附加记录：    

There's no reason to cut in mid-word, especially when we know what they said. Cutting in at  would make more sense.





D-6770:  I'm not letting you lay a fucking hair on him. Wait, did I say hair? I meant han-
附加记录：    

As much as I do like this line, it feels weird under pressure to go  when there's present danger. Recommend changing it to something more like:



D-6770:  I'm not letting you lay a fucking hair on him. I mean, han-
附加记录：    





SCP-5045-1:  [snip] Could you please put on the headset? It'll help me out a ton…

Researcher Ivan Hovnyuk:  You're just trying to get me to put the headset on, aren't you?
附加记录：    

Yes, obviously, as Farmer just said so.



That about wraps up everything that jumped out at me as no-good.








